cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language processing and neuroscience, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) since the paper evaluates different word embedding models for predicting neural activation patterns associated with concrete nouns. The second most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Learning), as the paper compares the performance of different embedding models. The third most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with machine learning models for natural language processing. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper evaluates neural models for word embeddings. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper discusses the use of brain imaging data for interpreting word embeddings.
